## Performance Tips

### Minimize Database Queries

**Bad (N+1 query):**
```csharp
// Application/Services/TodoService.cs
public async Task<IEnumerable<TodoDto>> GetAllTodosAsync()
{
    var todos = await _repository.GetAllAsync();
    
    foreach (var todo in todos)
    {
        // Separate query for each todo!
        var user = await _userRepository.GetByIdAsync(todo.UserId);
    }
}
```

**Good (single join):**
```csharp
// Infrastructure/Repositories/TodoRepository.cs
public async Task<IEnumerable<TodoItem>> GetAllWithUsersAsync()
{
    return await _context.TodoItems
        .Include(t => t.User)  // Single query with join
        .ToListAsync();
}
```

### Use AsNoTracking for Read-Only Queries

```csharp
// Infrastructure/Repositories/TodoRepository.cs
public async Task<IEnumerable<TodoItem>> GetAllAsync()
{
    return await _context.TodoItems
        .AsNoTracking()  // Faster, no change tracking
        .OrderByDescending(t => t.CreatedAt)
        .ToListAsync();
}
```

### Add Response Caching

```csharp
// Web/Controllers/HomeController.cs
[ResponseCache(Duration = 60)]
public async Task<IActionResult> Stats()
{
    var stats = await _todoService.GetStatsAsync();
    return PartialView("_Stats", stats);
}
```

### Database Indexing

In a migration:
```csharp
// Infrastructure/Migrations/xxx_AddIndexes.cs
protected override void Up(MigrationBuilder migrationBuilder)
{
    migrationBuilder.CreateIndex(
        name: "IX_TodoItems_IsComplete",
        table: "TodoItems",
        column: "IsComplete");
    
    migrationBuilder.CreateIndex(
        name: "IX_TodoItems_CreatedAt",
        table: "TodoItems",
        column: "CreatedAt");
}
```

